# tpd/

Intent's Technical Product Design (TPD) documentation — a comprehensive technical specification for the Intent system (formerly STP). The TPD is the authoritative design document covering requirements, architecture, implementation strategy, and deployment guidance for Intent v2.4.0, and serves as the preamble context for Claude on Intent projects.

## Files

- `technical_product_design.md` -- Master index and preamble to Claude; central entry point for all TPD sections
- `1_introduction.md` -- Purpose, scope, definitions, system overview, and version history
- `2_requirements.md` -- Functional and non-functional requirements with status and acceptance criteria
- `3_architecture.md` -- System architecture overview, component design, and layered structure
- `4_detailed_design.md` -- Directory structure, document templates, configuration system (as-built)
- `5_implementation_strategy.md` -- Development approach, steel thread breakdown, and task planning
- `6_deployment_and_operations.md` -- Installation methods, project initialization, environment setup (as-built)
- `7_technical_challenges_and_mitigations.md` -- LLM context management, portability, documentation maintenance strategies
- `8_appendices.md` -- Glossary, command reference, configuration schema, examples (as-built)
